Another consideration is the introduction of additional non-linearities or alternative activation functions. For instance, replacing ReLU with a Swish activation might offer smoother gradients and better performance on certain tasks. Additionally, experimenting with different layer configurations, such as adding batch normalization after the fully connected layers, could stabilize training and improve generalization.

Moreover, exploring the use of depth-wise separable convolutions instead of linear layers might provide a more efficient way to process spatial information, though this could alter the input-output tensor dimensions if not carefully implemented.

Finally, considering the addition of dropout layers could help prevent overfitting, especially when dealing with deeper networks or larger datasets.

